description:
From GEOFF JOHNS and GARY FRANK, the acclaimed team behind SUPERMAN: SECRET ORIGIN and the SHAZAM! stories in JUSTICE LEAGUE!

In the tradition of SUPERMAN: EARTH ONE, this spectacular original graphic novel gives new insight into BRUCE WAYNE'S transformation into BATMAN and his first year as THE DARK KNIGHT.

In this all new take on the Batman mythos, Bruce Wayne is on the hunt for his parents' killer. His target? The Mayor of Gotham City!

Plus, who is Alfred Pennyworth – and why is he so determined to put an end to the Batman?
name: Volume One

description:
Superman’s NEW secret identity revealed!

LOIS LANE continues her investigation into the mystery of Earth’s FIRST Superman!

Plus, in the backup story: We know where Superman got his armor costume, but where did he get all those “S” T-shirts?

Big things are in store for the next chapter in the Animal Man saga – and they start here!

Plus, the latest chapter in the TWO-FACE backup story.

“BREAKDOWN” part five!

Leaving California after having built a normal life, Brian Lazarus leaves everything behind and moves back to Florida's Everglades. Meanwhile the Man-Thing gets harassed by a bunch of strange fantastic beings whom origin is yet to be revealed!

description:
Fight or Flight continues!

A friend switches sides.

Cole becomes the hunted!

The long-awaited sequel to EVOLUTION

How did Sabretooth survive his beheading all those years ago?

The opening page of the book tells us that Sabretooth was presumed dead after he had his head took clean off by Wolverine, we jump back to New York where Wolverine is on a rescue mission to help Cloak who has been beaten and attached to the top of the Empire State Building, Cloak tells Wolverine that Sabretooth took his partner Dagger, Wolverine does not believe that to be possible knowing that he killed Sabretooth, but using Cloaks power of teleportation they investigate Sabretooths grave and find that his body still lies underneath the ground. Wolverine soon realizes it is a trap to lure him back to Silver Fox's house where Sabretooth murdered his lover long ago. He discovers Romulus is behind everything Cloak and Dagger flee the scene leaving Wolverine and Romulus to battle it out, Wolverine is near death when he is saved by a mysterious stranger who tells him answers lie in the Weapon X facility suddenly he passes out and when he awakes Romulus and the stranger are gone, Wolverine goes to explore the Weapon X facility only to find that someone has been experimenting with Sabretooths genetics and has cloned him more than 30 times, suddenly one wakes up who Wolverine recognizes the sent to be the real Sabretooth, he leaps toward Wolverine, "To Be Continued" ending.

description: Season 8 ended with a bang that cut the world off from magic—culminating in another set of world-ending problems. Buffy has left her best friend, Willow, powerless, and brought an end to a millennia-long tradition of superpowered girls. By day, Buffy is a twenty-something waitress with no real direction, and even though magic is gone, she’s still a vampire Slayer by night. Bigger problem? Vampires are becoming an epidemic . . . of zompires! Collects Buffy the Vampire Slayer Season 9 #1–#5.

description:
The celebrated pre-Code Crime Does Not Pay comics are finally collected into a series of unflinching and uncensored deluxe hardcovers! The infamous Crime Does Not Pay stories, focusing on criminal scum, nefarious mobsters, and urban legends, made Crime Does Not Pay one of the most popular comics of the 1940s. This series was a favorite target of censors and is partially responsible for the creation of the stifling Comics Code Authority! Revered, influential, and very hard to find, Crime Does Not Pay issues #26 to #29 are collected for your enjoyment and education!

Story Titles

description:
Trevor’s monstrous little brother lives in the barn behind the house. The boy’s only six years old, but he towers over his older brother, and possesses incredible strength. For years, Trevor has looked after his baby brother, keeping him from the light, but now that’s all about to change. His family’s secret is about to be revealed, uncovering the horrible truth of the small Midwestern town the boys have grown up in.

Collected in deluxe hardcover edition!

Winner of the Spectrum Gold Award!
name: HC

description:
The epic tale of blood and drool begins here! Join Molly and her dogs Mingo and Colfax, as she recounts the legend of "The Warrior and the Battlepug"—a tale of a fearless barbarian, his trusty and freakishly large pug, and evil baby harp seals. This volume collects the first year of Mike Norton’s Battlepug—the perfect opportunity to get in on the ground floor of the fan-favorite webcomic by Mike Norton, Allen Passalaqua, and Crank!

By famed Runaways artist Mike Norton!

Includes extras not seen on the website!

It’s a pugly job, but someone’s gotta do it!
name: Volume 1: Blood and Drool

description:
Jesse Marsh continues revolutionizing comics art, imbuing these action-packed adventures with a blend of grace and power that has rarely been matched! Whether swinging through Marsh’s beautifully rendered jungle, flying through the air atop his giant eagle, or battling marauders alongside his friends from all over Africa’s land of Pal-ul-don, Tarzan proves one of comics’ greatest heroes. And fifty issues in, Jesse Marsh keeps getting better! Reprinting Dell’s Tarzan #52–#56 and March of Comics #125, from 1954, for the first time.

Introduction by Ron Marz!
name: Vol. 11

volume.name: Edgar Rice Burroughs' Tarzan: The Jesse Marsh Years

description:

Asterix and Obelix decide to escort the druid until the timber of the Carnutes because the road is long and dangerous. During the meeting time of the Druids there is a truce with the Romans. Asterix and Obelix camped on the edge of the forest waiting for the end of the meeting and Getafix to escort back to the village.

A group of Goths hide in the forest of Carnutes to kidnap the druid who is elected as the best of the year with the help of magic to help them prepare for the invasion of Gaul and Rome. At the meeting, Getafix is chosen the best druid of the year so you get the Menhir of gold. As is proclaimed, the Goths fall on him and kidnap.

Asterix and his partner leave for the country of the barbarians in their search, but on the way they encounter a Roman patrol that defeat, but they take them for Goths and give notice of searching. Dress up as Romans to be left alone on his journey to the East.

Friends come to Germania where they are captured. In prison are to prepare and plan Getafix's magic potion for them and give it to the Goths, to remain forever fighting among themselves and thus forget to invade their neighbors. These conflicts are known as Asterixianas wars.

The trio returned to their village where they were received with great festivities.

description: After holding it a secret for ten years, Hellboy creator Mike Mignola finally reveals Abe Sapien's bizarre history. Introduced in the first Hellboy book and featured prominently in the film, Abe Sapien has remained one of the most intriguing mysteries of Mignola's celebrated work. The recent Hellboy film steered clear of any origin story for Abe so that the tale could be told in Plague of Frogs. The story of Abe's origins unfolds as the Bureau for Paranormal Research and Defense try to stop the monstrous frog men from the first Hellboy graphic novel, Seed of Destruction. The plague begins its spread across America, lending an apocalyptic new direction to Mignola's stories. Collecting the five-issue miniseries.

So the objects end up in the village of the irreducible. Because of this, both parents are thrown into prison in the city by the Romans.

In their eagerness to catch the objects, Pompey sent to a Roman actress, Actress, that with a few arrangements is the spitting image of Panacea, which for years she lived with her husband Tragicómix in the big city.

In the end, Pompey and his allies are discovered, as well as the Actress, although the latter ends up helping the Gauls to free her parents and undo the mess. When Julius Caesar in Gaul person, rewarded with a Caesar Asterix gold (her image), Asterix and the Actress gives it to its great performance.

description: The gala villagers visited by an individual who comes from afar, and travels on a flying carpet. He has traveled from India to seek the services of Cacofonix, and it sends rain on their land to prevent the sacrifice of the princess and prevent Dhale Kanya, the head of a sect comes to power. Thus, Asterix, Obelix and Cacofonix begin their journey to India.

description: To get the secret of the magic potion, Julius Caesar decided to resort to secret police chief Roman Fielhastalfinus (caricature of French actor Bernard Blier), who entrusts his best spy, Ceroceroséix, appear in person in the village and is done with the formula. Ceroceroséix (with a physical spoof Sean Connery, the first James Bond film) is druid (although the Romans used for revenge) and may receive their formula because, according to ancient tradition, passed from mouth only druid druid's ear. In parallel, the Phoenician merchant Economicrisis (in his second appearance after Asterix the Gladiator) returns to the village to sell their products, but forget to bring along "rock oil", one of the many ingredients of the magic potion. In order to get it before the Romans discovered it is impossible to continue making magic potion, Economicrisis back to Phoenicia with Asterix, Obelix and Dogmatix Ceroceroséix spy, who has not managed to gain the full confidence of Getafix and therefore tries to sabotage mission from within. The trip becomes an adventure through the lands of Phoenicia, Palestine and elsewhere in the Middle East, dotted with references to subjects as varied as film of espionage, the Bible, the 1973 oil crisis and the situation of permanent war between different countries, peoples and ethnic groups in the area.
name: La odisea de Astérix

description: A Gallic village is divided in two by a large ditch. Each half of the people have elected their leader, who wants to be president of all the people. While one seeks help from the Romans, the other sends a distress message to Vitalstatistix be transmitted to Asterix, Obelix and Getafix to solve the problem. Half the people are betrayed by the Romans, but our heroes are aided by the chief's son and the other half of the people. After this unpleasant experience, the people are reconciled under the leadership of a chief's son and daughter of the other. Asterix and the others become happy in their village.

description: It breathes a suspicious calm in the village gala, all of it due to the Romans go, after a campaign in Belgium, the Gaulish village to rest! Consequently, the proud chief Vitalstatistix irritated, especially after hearing that, according to Julius Caesar, the Belgians, and they are the bravest of all Gaul. Although Asterix Getafix and oppose the latter, along with Obelix accompany Vitalstatistix eventually to Belgium, where they meet, among others, and Vancomolóquix Gueusealámbix, principal leaders of the Belgian people. After eating with them, decided to organize a contest in which people demonstrate what Gallo is the strongest shattering, of course, Roman camps and claiming further that Julius Caesar arbitrate such competition.

description: Julius Caesar Gaius sends his agent to put Conjuncture the Gauls to modernity at all costs using economics as a means to achieve this goal. Seeing that Obelix has become rich and important selling menhirs to Key Conjuncture, all the people end up doing the same. Menhirs that the Romans paid each time at a higher price. When the finances of Rome are in the soil, kill Caesar ordered the acquisition of useless monoliths. The Roman camp near the village pay the piper, while everything returns to normal.

description: It all starts in the village, when the druid Getafix Ordenalfabétix fish asks for the magic potion. Ordenalfabétix he says he still has not come of Lutetia, and Asterix and Obelix decide to go fishing aboard a boat Geriatrix old. A storm carries them out to sea, and left standing in the middle of a dead calm. They have an encounter with pirates, who take away all the leading feast to celebrate the birthday of the master, in exchange for the ship sink them. Obelix eats anything but an apple, leaving a reserve is poor. Exhausted and hungry, on the verge of madness, Obelix thrown into the sea in search of wild boars and attempting to rescue him, Asterix loses control of the boat and are at the mercy of the waves. Dan with a tree and drag them tide. Reach what they believe is a Roman camp, unaware that they have been the first to reach the Americas. After living some time with the native Indians who they believe are so rare Roman dresses, some Vikings also come to this earth and taken as a sign of discovery Asterix and Obelix. Already in the Nordic lands, a Gallic slave tells them where they are already on board his boat reach the coasts of Armorica, where they wait for their friends.

description:
The story begins in Rome, in a tavern where he is arrested on drunken legionnaire Romeomontescus, just hours of receiving your honest missio by 20 years of service to the Roman legion, under the charge of insulting the Julius Caesar himself. Because of this, Caesar decides to offer an honest anyway to Romeomontescus missio, a small detail: it is the Gaulish village where Asterix and his friends live.

Romeomontescus part and to the Gaul, and on the road gets drunk in the inn Ortopédix, and when it comes time to pay the innkeeper gives him ownership of the village as the price of a meal and some wine. Angina Ortopédix and decide to live at the village with the excuse that the air of an inn is not good to raise her teenage daughter Zaza. Once in town, the family hopes to enforce their property rights to the people showing the plate, signed by Caesar.

description: The Gallic stronghold is in full celebration of the Battle of Gergovia and to celebrate, invite all those rebels of the various places they visited in the previous albums. Before they arrive, Asterix and Obelix go in search of a Roman camp to offer their foreign friends. It seems that there are none but, just before leaving their camp, men receive an exile Pastelalrhum Corsican Ocatarinetabelachitchix, who must monitor them. The Gauls are discovered and, after the beating, decide to take with the prisoner, who decided to accompany his land for reunification with his family and, incidentally, achieved with the tribe overcome differences Figatélix Corsican, who quarrel for a long time ago, fighting against the Romans who run the island from the settlement of Aleria.

description:
On a stormy day the whole village gala is held in the house of his head Vitalstatistix fearing that the sky will collapse on their heads. At that moment, a fortune teller who gets to win the confidence of the people, less than our hero Asterix and the druid Getafix. The seer, in alliance with the Romans persuaded the Gauls to leave the village. A potion Getafix convince the rest of the people of their mistake after a ruse and return in pursuit of the Romans.

As a curiosity about this book is to realize that there is an explicit allusion to a painting by Rembrandt. Just look at the last bullet on page 10 and see that it is the painting "The Anatomy Lesson."

This is the only Asterix stories in which the Romans manage to occupy the village because its inhabitants abandoned the superstitions that gives them the seer. In fact, the centurion of Compendium, Caius Norterajus, have the luxury of sending an emissary to Rome to send a message to Julius Caesar: "All Gaul is occupied." The occupation is very short due to the magic of Panoramix, which makes the lining back to their camp.
name: El adivino

description: During a dinner at the home of brother of the chief of Gaul, he and Obelix get drunk and boast that they are able to serve a stew with the laurel crown of Caesar. So Asterix and Obelix head for Rome to serve this stew, but it endangers their lives, since it is not easy to steal the object.
name: Los laureles del César

description: Julius Caesar is the idea of ​​building a luxury development next to the Gaulish village where Asterix lives, in order that the village will end up being a shantytown. Unfortunately for the tenants of the Residence of the Gods, Cacofonix moves into one of the floors.
name: La residencia de los dioses

description:
The prefect of Condate (Rennes), Graco Ojoalvirus, leads a life of luxury in the orgies abound thanks to swindle large amounts of taxes paid by the city to Julius Caesar. Due to the few coins that Condate sent to Rome, the government begins to suspect the attitude of Ojoalvirus and sends the quaestor (collector) Claudius Sinusitus to report possible tax irregularities in the area. This is received in an apparently cordial Ojoalvirus, but soon after he is poisoned. Rejecting the attention of the Roman physicians distrust of them, Sinusitus seeks help from the nearby village gala.

There, Getafix informs you that you need to cure a silver star (edelweiss), a plant that only grows in the mountain peaks of Helvetia (Switzerland), where Asterix and Obelix travel. During his journey through Gaul, the Romans let them go freely, but to reach Helvetia begin to suffer the persecution of the legions because the governor of the region and Ojoalvirus friend, Key Diplodocus, want to fail in his mission. Despite the impediments of Diplodocus, Asterix and Obelix manage to cross Geneva (Geneva), Lake Lemanus and eventually take over the plant in a nearby summit to returning to cure Sinusitus, thanks to the invaluable help of several Helvetii as Guardiasuix innkeeper, the banker Zúrix and a group of Tyrolean mountaineers. Thanks to the Silver Star, Sinusitus recovers, drinks the magic potion and gives it its deserved Ojoalvirus, then order the detention of this and Diplodocus. Sinusitus is the first and only Roman in The Adventures of Asterix is ​​attending as a guest to the traditional evening meal that occurs at the end of all the albums.

As in his travels to other countries, the Helvetii are characterized by a number of topics: his obsession with cleanliness (which causes the wrath of Cayo Diplodocus, which does not comprehend a feast is also fun if not greasy), the accuracy of their clocks (though not cuckoo, but sand), cheese with holes, the secrecy of his bank, his love for climbing and obsession to maintain neutrality in most conflicts and assist the wounded of all sides (to the extent that when they finally decide to face the Romans, heal wounds). It also appears a monumental building that brings together representatives of all the tribes of central Europe to discuss politics (although most of these are just sleeping), an ancient precedent of the United Nations.
name: Astérix en Helvecia

description: In the Gallic village, incredibly, the calm is seen in the environment, which causes it to be tense in the Senate of Rome. One of the senators, Stradivarius, complains that while Julius Caesar wants the conquests extend Roman territory, is not capable of ensuring peace in which you have already conquered, which reminds him of the strength of Asterix and company. To do this, some of Caesar's aides suggest, knowing the union between the inhabitants of the redoubt, that someone sow discord between them so that, in this way, the force that makes them stay together (higher even than the potion) is neglected and thus, can conquer the territory. This "grower" of weed, Roman prisoner who promised freedom if he gets the disintegration of the village, called Detritus and try with all their wickedness, make friends and break the peace galas. Once it reaches the village, Asterix gives a significant value for ceramic Caius Aerobus, the head of the Roman camp Aquarium, considering the Gallic hero as the main man of the village, offending Vitalstatistix and, above all, his wife Impedimenta . From there, the atmosphere will thin to the point where Asterix and Obelix are close to breaking his great friendship, but the confrontation arose between them will be nothing but nonsense. Asterix, Obelix and Getafix devise a plan for the Romans themselves end up going to jail Detritus and things take their course.

description: Deaf Nohive troops they have held and conquer almost the whole of Spain, except for a small Iberian village halfway between Munda and Hispalis, not waiver from their roots. To end the resistance, the Romans captured Pepe (although Pericles real name), the son, moody and rude, of Sopalajo of Arriérez and bacon, the Iberian chief, on condition that he returned to his father if left to conquer. While Romans head to Rome, they find Asterix and Obelix, who decided to snatch the child and return to Spain. By the way, the Gauls are the pirates in the Atlantic, with tourists from northern Europe, with processions and bullfights druids in the Spanish territory and Gypsy dance and sing around the fire, while one of the Romans , Nonpossumus, disguised, intended to steal the magic potion and return the child to the Romans. Even briefly appears a kind of Celtiberian version of Don Quixote and Sancho Panza.
name: Astérix en Hispania

description:
Chief Gaul Asterix Moralelástix entrusts the care of a cauldron full of sesterces, so that money does not fall into the hands of the tax collector for the Roman Empire. The custody of Asterix, the money is stolen, leaving only the empty pot with onion soup flavor. As the situation compromises the honor of the village against another Gallic chief, Asterix is banished, unless you return the money disappeared. Autodestierra and Obelix accompany his friend to fill the pot of money again and repair the fault.

Asterix and Obelix trying to recover the money without success and in many ways. Among them, crush the pirates, who for once were trying to establish an honest business, to turn your boat into a restaurant. The duo also relies on the sale of pigs, the fight, action, gambling and even try to rob a bank, which has run out of funds because of tax increases of the Romans.

In the end, they encounter a Roman tax collector, who steal, but when you have to bring money Moralelástix, Asterix suspect you smell on coins. The pot had been used previously to prepare onion soup, and coins that the collector had issued charging that smell.

Asterix and Obelix target Moralelástix village, located near a coastal bluff. Asterix faces Moralelástix since been found to Moralelástix had stolen their own money, paid taxes to the Romans to continue to have good relations with them and used them to recover. Continuing a feud between villagers and Obelix and Asterix and his head between, ending with the pot of money falling off the cliff, which concludes the scene.

However, the money falls into the ship of the pirates, who for once just the adventure with a happy ending. Asterix and Obelix return to their village in triumph.
name: Astérix y el caldero

description:
One day in late spring, was picking mushrooms Vegestorix Roman camp near the Aquarium when he heard loud cries of joy that came from the Roman site. Gluteus Maximus was selected to represent them in the Olympics.

Vegestorix reported this news in the village and soon learned that the Olympic Games consisted of a sacred truce maintained while developed various athletic events in the Greek city of Olympia. The games were held every four years in the month of hecatombeon and lasted five days.

Gluteus Maximus was training in the woods when crossed with Asterix and Obelix beat it on all the evidence, returned to camp very demoralized and told his centurion, Tulius Borricus, not wanting to participate in the games because he was overcome by two Gauls in the forest.

Tulius Borricus went to the village of the Gauls and met with the head Vitalstatistix who asked that his train left Gauls quiet Mulus their champion. The Gallic chief replied that he would think and answer. Vitalstatistix, meeting with the villagers decided it best that they also participate in games, since the potion could win any event. Vitalstatistix was the Roman camp and told the centurion Borricus decided, but replied that the games were reserved only for the Greeks and Romans.

Sorry Vitalstatistix returned to the village with the news, but Asterix found the solution: they, from the conquest of Gaul by Julius Caesar, were also Romans. In the village everyone wanted to be the representatives, but there was a problem, the qualifying ended in a draw, since the potion gave equal force to each. Finally they decided that their representatives would be Asterix games, being the most intelligent and who had the idea, and Obelix to have the strength continuously. In addition, all the men of the village accompany them to Greece.

Immediately began preparations in the village: Vitalstatistix handled the trip, hire a good galley, Getafix the technical preparation of athletes; Cacofonix ceremonial. After a pleasant journey, they had to make galley slaves and an encounter with pirates, finally arrived in Piraeus, the port of Athens. In Athens, while touring the monuments, they found their "compatriots" Roman Aquarium. In the ballroom he said he stood Vegestorix ten years younger, now felt as a young man of 83.

Finally they reached the city aa games, Olympia, the sacred city with its temple to Zeus and the statue made by Phidias, one of the wonders of the world. Garmonparnas, the judge told them that in Olympic games competitors are prohibited from taking any substance capable of providing additional forces under penalty of disqualification. The Gauls decide to compete without the magic potion for Asterix represented.

In competitions triumphed only Greek athletes. Sopaconondas, Olympic president of the Senate, spoke to the senators the problem facing them in the future if only his athletes triumphed, tourism would decline, because the Romans would not want to continue attending. Sopaconondas he proposed as a solution, make a career just to Romans, and would at least have a winner.

Asterix and Getafix had the idea to induce the Romans to drink the magic potion with what would be disqualified, what actually happened. All the Romans came together to the finish and Asterix behind. The Gauls claimed that there was cheating in the race because the Romans had used a potion, the judges did show them the language and we all had blue sign that had taken a drink prohibited, unless the Asterix and he was proclaimed champion and received the Palme d'Or.

The Gauls returned to his village in the same ship that had brought them to Greece and the reception party when asked Asterix to show the Palme d'Or, it said that it had been a gift to someone who needed it more than he . Julius Caesar, in Rome, very happy with the win in the Olympics Gluteus Maximus had risen to centurion and Tulius Borricus a tribune.
name: Astérix y los juegos olímpicos

description:
After the defeat gala hands of the Romans at the battle of Alesia, the leader of the Gauls, Vercingetorix, deposited "in the feet" of Julius Caesar his shield as a symbol of surrender. Caesar leaves left the shield, which passes successively through the hands of a Roman archer, a legionnaire, a centurion drunk, the owner of a tavern and an anonymous Gallic warrior survivor.

Some years later, in the village gala Vitalstatistix suffers a liver disease caused by excesses in the final banquet. To seek a cure, Asterix and Obelix accompany his boss to a spa in Nemessos (now Clermont-Ferrand), a city in the country Chieftain.

While the head remains in the spa, Asterix and Obelix advantage for touring the region. During his trip, have a meeting about Gergovia with "Tulius Bolígrafus, special envoy of Julius Caesar." Asterix, offended by the arrogance that displays it, decides to stop his march and his entourage to mamporros. After the meeting know the wine merchant and coal Alámbix, who sympathized with them after seeing Bolígrafus have defeated, decides to give inn at home.

Caesar learned of this "second loss" of Gergovia, finally decides to chasten Gauls Gergovia celebrating a victory in the Gallic manner, that is, parading on the shield of Vercingetorix. Viewing Tulius Bolígrafus that the shield is not among the possessions of the campaigns of Caesar, and warned by him to find the real coat ("I can not celebrate my victory rather than on the Chieftain's Shield! Is useless to try to fool me! Bluff Caesar is to trick the gods, and the anger of the gods is terrible! "), the Romans undertake a desperate search to locate it.

The Gauls find out the intentions of the Romans through a spy drunk Alámbix visit the tavern in search of information, but that leaves the tongue after a few drinks. Alarmed, Asterix decides to start his own search for the Chieftain's Shield to avoid giving to Caesar that triumph.

description:
A zombie anthology spanning time and space, with stories from pre-historic Earth, the Roman Empire, World War 1, Future Earth, Aliens and more! Aliens land on planet Earth in our not-too-distant future and find a desolate planet. In order to discover what caused the devastation the aliens enter a museum and are able to look into Earth's past using the artifacts on display.

Story Titles

  • Tar
  • Flesh Of My Flesh
  • Under the Sand
  • Freedom Blood, Brotherhood
  • Zombie World War 1
  • The Dark Side of the Moon
  • Bonus Track

Asterix and the unseen is a volume of the Asterix comic series created by Albert Uderzo (Drawings) and Rene Goscinny (Guion). This comic is a collection of fourteen stories, which were published in Spain only forty years after its original release in France.

She's walking death. A goddess of carnage. Bare-handed she's unbelievable but put a gun in her hand? You'd have to be out of your mind. Elsewhere... the newly elected Prez is accused of fraud on Election Day by the candidate that lost.

The bodies begin piling up as the world's governments move against the forces of the teenage superheroes. Meanwhile, Kid Vigilante is concerned about the link between Jack Fearless and the President of the United States.
